latestIgtvVideos.caption:
This has to be my parent's favourite song. They've never said it but i have grown up listening to it enough to understand. The last few months have been nostalgic and i have been trying to capture as much as i can.  This was unplanned,made by luck on a rainy day where emotions were as fluid as the water,but not as tasteless.
*Earphones recommended*

latestPosts.caption:
As Naina wisely says, “Jahan ho wahan ka maza lo.”

It’s so easy to overlook such moments of beauty, especially when we’re caught up in the hustle of our daily lives. We often rush past these fleeting experiences, missing the opportunity to truly appreciate them in their purest form. 

One of the most breathtaking sunsets I experienced was in Kashmir. The scene was filled with a serene beauty that created a profound sense of calm within me. In that moment, I felt completely content and at peace with everything around me.
